                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>Columbia <add>S.C.</add></placeName>
                                        <date>March 12<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1848</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>Dear Sir</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">I throw aside all manner of reserve<lb/> and
                                        address you for the purpose of gaining informa-<lb/>tion on
                                        a certain Chapter in the Holy Book; had it not<lb/> been
                                        pointed out to me by a Revd gentleman of the<lb/> Christian
                                        denomination, with a view to obtain <hi rend="underline">his
                                                  end</hi>.<lb/> I do not think I would have
                                        encroached upon your time,<lb/> but as it does come up in
                                        the form of a strong argument<lb/> as he remarks in <hi
                                                  rend="underline">his favor</hi>, I would be
                                        pleased to hear your<lb/> views in regards to it. I venture,
                                        or rather choose not to enter<lb/> into argument until I
                                        hear from you feeling certain that one<lb/> so able and
                                        distinguished as yourself, one so well versed in<lb/>
                                        biblical lore can easily explain it. I have reference to
                                        the<lb/> 53 chapter of Isaiah, a gentleman by the name of
                                                  <persName>Abrahams</persName> from <placeName>New
                                                  York</placeName> endeavored to explain it in the
                                        Sunday School<lb/> but his explanation was not satisfactory
                                        to me, <hi rend="underline">not that I</hi><lb/>
                                        <hi rend="underline">doubt</hi> for I am a Jew, a real
                                        Israelite in every sense<lb/> of the word, and proud am I of
                                        the name. There is<lb/> another circumstance connected with
                                        this chapter which<lb/> casts a gloom over me <sic>when
                                                  ever</sic> I see it, in confidence<lb/> I reveal
                                        it; my brother in law (<persName>Mr Isaac Woolfs
                                                  son</persName> of<lb/>
                                        <placeName>Charleston</placeName>) became <hi
                                                  rend="underline">converted</hi> to Christianity on
                                        that very<lb/> chapter, nor was there any one who could
                                        sufficiently<lb/> explain it as to prove to him that the
                                        construction he placed<lb/> on it was false, do you not
                                        think great good and benefit</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>would arise from it were you to give an explanation in<lb/> your
                                        valuable Advocate of Jewish Rights <sic>“</sic> the
                                        Occident?</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I should be pleased to hear from you by<lb/>
                                        return of mail, or as early as convenient, and if you
                                        differ<lb/> with me as regards a public explanation, trust
                                        you will give me<lb/> your views in answer to this, by so
                                        doing you will oblige many<lb/> of your friends here, and
                                        none more so than</p>
                              <p rend="indent(10)">Your Obt Sert &amp; Well Wisher</p>
                              <p rend="indent(10)">
                                        <persName role="author">L. T. Levin</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>
